                    <persName xml:id="name1216-3" xml:lang="fr-x-fiey" source="#bib1216-1">LES
                        ÉGYPTIENS DE QARTMĪN</persName>
                    <idno type="URI">http://syriaca.org/person/1216</idno>
                    <idno type="FIEY">135</idno>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" resp="http://syriaca.org" corresp="http://syriaca.org/persons http://syriaca.org/q">In hagiography: the
                        “Egyptians of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/226">Qartmin</placeName>” were a group of 800 monks from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> who were buried at
                            <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/226">Qartmin</placeName>. Their
                        legend was connected to the crania in the monastery <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/226">Qartmin</placeName>. Eight hundred
                        princes on pilgrimage from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/715">Egypt</placeName> became monks of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/226">Qartmin</placeName>.</note>
                    <floruit>
